        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-jan-13-2.jpg" alt="Deflation persists in China" href="https://www.altdaily.co" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">China’s economy remains entrenched in deflationary territory as producer prices fell for the 26th consecutive month in November. The producer price index dropped 2.5% year-on-year. Meanwhile, consumer inflation slowed to just 0.2% growth, its weakest pace since June. The GDP deflator also remains subdued, reflecting tepid demand across various sectors.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The Chinese government’s stimulus measures have stabilized market sentiments but failed to revive the deteriorating economic conditions. The deflationary trend raises the likelihood of additional stimulus measures, including potential interest rate cuts and liquidity injections.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
