          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
            <strong>🇮🇹 Ferrari Group eyes IPO in Europe</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Ferrari Group is <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-13-01-2025-wn1-3-considering-an-ipo" target="_blank">considering an IPO</a>. Goldman Sachs is advising on the potential listing, which could happen this year. Founded in Italy in 1959, Ferrari Group posted $341 million in revenue and $88.8M in EBITDA in 2023. With European IPO activity expected to rebound, Ferrari joins other family-owned businesses like Germany’s Pfisterer Holding in seeking public listings.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
