          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
            <strong>🇨🇳 Chinese stocks stumble on weak start</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Chinese equities saw their <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-13-01-2025-wn3-5-worst-new-year-start" target="_blank">worst New Year’s start</a> since 2016.  The CSI 300 Index fell 2.9%, and the Hang Seng Enterprises Index dropped 3.1% on Thursday. Weak manufacturing data and looming US tariff hikes fueled investor caution. Despite last year’s late stimulus-driven gains, market sentiment remains fragile. Analysts are bracing for further volatility as traders brace for potential stimulus during China’s annual legislative session in March.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
