        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Emerging markets face currency intervention challenges:</strong> Emerging-market central banks are <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-13-01-2025-m6-11-battling-currency-volatility" target="_blank">battling currency volatility</a> as fiscal policies lag. China’s PBOC is defending the yuan through tight monetary controls in Asia. Latin American central banks intervene heavily to stabilize currencies like Brazil’s real. Analysts warn that stronger fiscal measures are required to stop further devaluation.</p>
